Dialogue: 2,0:02:27.21,0:02:33.26,Mushisode Title,,0,0,0,eptitle,{\an6\fad(2000,0)\blur0.6\pos(1137,110)}The Cushion of Grass
Dialogue: 5,0:02:41.68,0:02:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What are you?
Dialogue: 5,0:02:51.85,0:02:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Are you planning on eating me?
Dialogue: 5,0:02:59.75,0:03:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Are you afraid of me?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:07.35,0:03:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nah, you're just watching me...
Dialogue: 5,0:03:16.97,0:03:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and trying to figure out what I am.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:51.17,0:03:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, looks like you're human after all.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:56.05,0:03:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Green eyes...
Dialogue: 5,0:03:58.80,0:04:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and white hair.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:02.15,0:04:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard of you.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:04.95,0:04:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,"There is a unnatural child who attracts mushi and causes disasters wherever he goes."
Dialogue: 5,0:04:12.32,0:04:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I've also heard that plenty of mushi-shi have taken you in.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:15.38,0:04:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Did another one throw you out or something?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:20.06,0:04:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Why stick around and let mushi get lured in?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:23.53,0:04:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You can prevent disasters from happening as long as you keep moving, you know.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:29.55,0:04:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I do it to earn my keep.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:32.00,0:04:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I attract mushi, and the mushi-shi resolves whatever problems arise.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:36.78,0:04:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that every now and then, \Nthings get out of hand.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:41.64,0:04:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are the kind of people \Nwho usually take you in, huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:49.09,0:04:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Suguro.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:50.87,0:04:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a mushi-shi who lives in these mountains.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:54.94,0:04:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 5,0:04:59.49,0:05:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:00.90,0:05:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A Tokoyami, or "Eternal Darkness" mushi, \Nis trapped here.{Tokoyami: Eternal darkness}
Dialogue: 5,0:05:05.90,0:05:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You were probably swallowed by one in the past.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:09.91,0:05:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That explains your peculiar constitution as well.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:13.59,0:05:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A Tokoyami?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:15.44,0:05:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,None of the other mushi-shi told you{ about it}?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:17.90,0:05:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a mushi as pitch-black as pure darkness.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:20.98,0:05:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Your memories before a certain point \Nhave disappeared too, right?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:24.40,0:05:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It also eats memories.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:27.11,0:05:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you take it out,
Dialogue: 5,0:05:29.32,0:05:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll become normal again, right?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:32.33,0:05:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a mushi trapped in your body.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:35.31,0:05:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Tokoyami don't attract other mushi.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:39.55,0:05:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to say, but that's all you.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:43.37,0:05:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,People like you crop up every so often,
Dialogue: 5,0:05:46.50,0:05:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but no one's ever found a way to treat that condition.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:50.94,0:05:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, all you can do is accept it.{'that reality', but reuse of 'that'}
Dialogue: 5,0:05:59.35,0:06:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, I scattered the mushi that were surrounding you.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:02.23,0:06:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It should hold for a few days.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:04.69,0:06:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Before you go, you should regain your strength \Nso you don't collapse again.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:12.99,0:06:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a River of Light here?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:17.21,0:06:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there is.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:20.49,0:06:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Then... that must have been the mountain lord.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:28.34,0:06:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to keep an eye on me, you know.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:31.31,0:06:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like I'm going to settle down here.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:51.41,0:06:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"Ginko," was it?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:53.81,0:06:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're well enough to walk, come with me.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:12.12,0:07:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Did they teach you anything about basic herbs, at least?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:16.00,0:07:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A bit.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:18.05,0:07:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The herbs on this mountain are especially potent.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:20.94,0:07:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Take some with you.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:24.13,0:07:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn how to make mushi-repellent cigarettes yourself, too.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:27.36,0:07:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't just lessen the effect you have on your surroundings.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:31.95,0:07:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll also protect you from \Nany mushi-related diseases.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:55.13,0:07:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,A beautiful place, isn't it?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:00.13,0:08:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't let you stay for long,
Dialogue: 5,0:08:02.31,0:08:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but if you stop by \Nonce in a while just to say hello,
Dialogue: 5,0:08:04.32,0:08:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure the mountain lord won't mind too much.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:18.58,0:08:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Suguro.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:20.62,0:08:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:22.04,0:08:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That boy's not from around here, is he?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:24.78,0:08:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just looking after him for a little while.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:29.41,0:08:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You could say he's my apprentice.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:31.88,0:08:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, where are your manners?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:34.98,0:08:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:37.13,0:08:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:38.32,0:08:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, good luck to you, kiddo.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:41.00,0:08:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how are things looking?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:42.69,0:08:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we have a new mountain lord yet?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:45.12,0:08:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:47.80,0:08:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't a new one have been born by now?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:50.44,0:08:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 5,0:08:52.00,0:08:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Come now, there's no reason to be so concerned.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:55.67,0:08:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Worrying won't make a difference.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:57.60,0:09:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The flowers will bloom \Nand bear fruit like they do every year.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:01.23,0:09:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's simply the natural order of things.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:12.37,0:09:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What was all that talk about a new mountain lord?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:20.10,0:09:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Even mountain lords are mortal.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:23.16,0:09:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The one here is nearing the end of its life.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:28.45,0:09:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But for some reason, we still \Nhaven't seen any sign of its successor.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:34.09,0:09:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's no lord when this one dies, these mountains will decline.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:38.47,0:09:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what has everyone so worried.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:42.85,0:09:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If one never showed up, what would that mean?{reworded this slightly to make it clearer that no new lord is a symptom more than the direct cause of the world declining}
Dialogue: 5,0:09:47.74,0:09:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In time, the whole world would fall apart.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:51.86,0:09:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like I mentioned.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:53.50,0:09:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The lack of a mountain lord would be like flowers not blooming in the springtime.{technically this "flowers" should be possessive (with an apostrophe: flowers'), but that would probably distract people more than being technically incorrect, so it's left out. http://www.quickanddirtytips.com/education/grammar/do-i-hate-your-singing-or-you-singing}
Dialogue: 5,0:09:59.70,0:10:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They are embodiments of the natural order of life.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:04.28,0:10:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Mountain lords signify the bond between \Nthe mountains and the natural order itself.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:27.50,0:10:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:29.14,0:10:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The mountain lord isn't watching me anymore.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:42.38,0:10:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:46.99,0:10:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the mountain lord has passed away.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:51.77,0:10:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go take a look around.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:53.30,0:10:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You stay here.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:57.41,0:10:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Did this happen because of me{I showed up}?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:00.80,0:11:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you it was on its last legs?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:03.84,0:11:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,However, its successor still hasn't appeared.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:07.55,0:11:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's unrest in the mountains.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:09.32,0:11:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You should stay here.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:12.22,0:11:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:35.11,0:11:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:39.39,0:11:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 5,0:12:02.49,0:12:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this egg... belong to the mountain lord?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:09.25,0:12:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:14.68,0:12:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a successor after all.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:32.48,0:12:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}All the mountain lord's power lies inside this little egg.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:40.86,0:12:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It{ is a being that}'s the complete opposite of me.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:45.82,0:12:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's... the chosen one.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:57.74,0:12:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I...
Dialogue: 5,0:13:01.75,0:13:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I were to act right now, \Ncould I make its power mine?{pls}
Dialogue: 5,0:13:13.62,0:13:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't be foolish.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:15.93,0:13:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What the hell are you thinking?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:39.61,0:13:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What the...
Dialogue: 5,0:13:42.56,0:13:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:57.63,0:13:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I do?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:59.38,0:14:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I...
Dialogue: 5,0:14:02.34,0:14:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Suguro.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:04.45,0:14:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Suguro!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:16.47,0:14:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Its light is getting fainter.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:21.60,0:14:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I don't do something quick...
Dialogue: 5,0:14:29.93,0:14:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Mountain Lord?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:32.06,0:14:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You're alive!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:33.85,0:14:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, please tell me what to do!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:36.61,0:14:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:38.26,0:14:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, come back!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:40.98,0:14:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You know everything, don't you?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:43.58,0:14:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, I'll do anything!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:45.90,0:14:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as I can fix this,
Dialogue: 5,0:14:48.86,0:14:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter what happens to me!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:36.42,0:15:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The River of Light...
Dialogue: 5,0:15:52.86,0:15:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mountain Lord!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:55.72,0:15:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:05.78,0:16:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no...
Dialogue: 5,0:16:36.92,0:16:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I...
Dialogue: 5,0:16:40.10,0:16:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}enter that place,
Dialogue: 5,0:16:41.88,0:16:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}then I probably won't be able to come back.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:47.87,0:16:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But that doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:53.31,0:16:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I mean, it's not like I belong anywhere anyway.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:07.36,0:17:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Tokoyami is struggling.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:11.67,0:17:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 5,0:17:13.46,0:17:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you always get in my way?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:28.74,0:17:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:34.14,0:17:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You just want to live.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:49.12,0:18:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Did it just tell me to go back?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:57.94,0:19:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Do I... even deserve to go back?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:06.43,0:19:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)\alpha&H40&}Hey!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:09.40,0:19:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)\alpha&H40&}Ginko!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:23.12,0:19:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginko!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:24.08,0:19:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You're{ alive}...
Dialogue: 5,0:19:25.77,0:19:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:29.11,0:19:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:33.49,0:19:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:50.61,0:19:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:53.33,0:19:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,These mountains will have to shut down \Nfor the time being, then.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:59.83,0:20:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the natural order gone forever?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:04.37,0:20:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going to happen to these mountains?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:09.94,0:20:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What you saw back there was the natural order itself.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:14.21,0:20:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think of the mountain lords as flowers blooming on the surface, what you saw are their roots.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:21.39,0:20:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Since they accepted the mountain lord's life,
Dialogue: 5,0:20:25.02,0:20:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm certain another will appear again someday.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:30.92,0:20:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, you should get ready to leave.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:35.06,0:20:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't forgive you for what you've done.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:39.56,0:20:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope I never see you again.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:03.48,0:21:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Might as well call it a day here.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:15.25,0:21:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope I never see you again.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:20.85,0:21:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you shouldn't forget:
Dialogue: 5,0:21:25.40,0:21:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no place in this world where we don't belong.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:31.71,0:21:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That includes you.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:33.79,0:21:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The natural order let you come back.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:39.94,0:21:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter where you go, you'll always belong there.
